    pearls: ["Pitting edema grading: 1+ (2 mm, immediate rebound), 2+ (4 mm, 15 seconds), 3+ (6 mm, 30 seconds), 4+ (8+ mm, greater than 30 seconds) -- always use consistent 5-second press over bony prominence","Non-pitting edema does NOT respond to diuretics -- positive Stemmer sign differentiates lymphedema (requires compression therapy) from cardiac edema (responds to diuretics)","A weight gain of 1 kg equals approximately 1 liter of retained fluid -- daily weights are MORE accurate than I&O for tracking fluid balance","Unilateral leg edema with calf tenderness = DVT until proven otherwise -- do NOT massage the extremity (risk of dislodging clot causing PE)","Always check the sacrum in bedbound patients -- gravity causes fluid to accumulate in dependent areas, and pedal edema may be absent despite significant fluid retention"],
